 --> <div class="w3-hide-large" style="margin-top: 83px;"></div> <!-- Top header for large screens --> <header class="w3-container w3-xlarge sticky-header" style="padding-top: 16px; padding-right: 16px; padding-bottom: 16px; padding-left: 16px; background-color: #1e88e5; color: white;"> <p class="w3-left logo" style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Wealixir Policies</p> <div class="search-container" style="position: relative; display: flex; left: 500px; top: 20px;"> <input type="text" id="search" placeholder="Search..." oninput="searchContent()" class="search-bar" style="border-top-width: 3px; border-bottom-width: 3px; border-left-width: 3px; border-top-style: solid; border-bottom-style: solid; border-left-style: solid; border-top-color: rgb(0, 180, 204); border-bottom-color: rgb(0, 180, 204); border-left-color: rgb(0, 180, 204); border-image-source: initial; border-image-slice: initial; border-image-width: initial; border-image-outset: initial; border-image-repeat: initial; border-right-width: initial; border-right-style: none; border-right-color: initial; padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 10px; padding-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 10px; height: 40px; border-top-left-radius: 5px; border-top-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-left-radius: 5px; outline-color: initial; outline-style: none; outline-width: initial; color: rgb(157, 191, 175);" /><button class="search-button" onclick="searchContent()" style="width: 40px; height: 40px; border-top-width: 1px; border-right-width: 1px; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-left-width: 1px; border-top-style: solid; border-right-style: solid; border-bottom-style: solid; border-left-style: solid; border-top-color: rgb(0, 180, 204); border-right-color: rgb(0, 180, 204); border-bottom-color: rgb(0, 180, 204); border-left-color: rgb(0, 180, 204); border-image-source: initial; border-image-slice: initial; border-image-width: initial; border-image-outset: initial; border-image-repeat: initial; background-image: initial; background-position-x: initial; background-position-y: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: rgb(0, 180, 204); text-align: center; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border-top-left-radius: 0px; border-top-right-radius: 5px; border-bottom-right-radius: 5px; border-bottom-left-radius: 0px; cursor: pointer; font-size: 20px;"><i class="fa fa-search"></i></button> </div> </header> <!-- download button --><!-- <a href="path/to/your/download/file.pdf" download class="download-button"> <i class="fa fa-download"></i> Download </a> --><!-- Up button --><a href="#" onclick="scrollToTop()" class="up-button" style="position: fixed; right: 20px; bottom: 20px; width: 50px; height: 50px; background-image: linear-gradient(45deg, rgb(30, 136, 229), rgb(255, 152, 0)); background-position-x: initial; background-position-y: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; color: white; text-align: center; line-height: 50px; border-top-left-radius: 50%; border-top-right-radius: 50%; border-bottom-right-radius: 50%; border-bottom-left-radius: 50%; box-shadow: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3) 0px 4px 8px; z-index: 1000; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; font-size: 24px; transition-behavior: normal, normal, normal; transition-duration: 0.3s, 0.3s, 0.3s; transition-timing-function: ease, ease, ease; transition-delay: 0s, 0s, 0s; transition-property: background, transform, opacity; opacity: 0;"><i class="fa fa-arrow-up" style="margin-top: 3px;"></i></a ><!-- About Section --> <div id="about" class="w3-container searchable-content" style="padding-top: 16px; padding-right: 16px; padding-bottom: 16px; padding-left: 16px;"> <h2 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229); border-bottom-width: 2px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(255, 152, 0);">About Wealixir</h2> <div id="brief" class="searchable-content"> <h3 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229);">Brief About Wealixir</h3> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;"><strong>Wealixir</strong> as we know today is fusion of three companies <strong>Shree Associates, CA Santosh Poojary and V&amp;G Capital</strong> and has built itself on the three verticals of <strong>Insurance, Investments and Taxation.</strong></p> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Wealixir currently is running smoothly with a team of 30 people which has a rich blend of mature experienced people as well as new energetic creative millennials.</p> </div> <div id="vision" class="searchable-content"> <h3 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229);">Wealixir Vision</h3> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Be a Distinctive Financial Planning Company, with focus on Life Insurance, providing family centric, personalized and holistic planning with unparalleled service.</p> </div> <div id="mission" class="searchable-content"> <h3 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229);">Wealixir Mission</h3> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Our mission is to bring happiness and self‐reliance to every family helping them become financially independent and exceeding our client’s service expectations.</p> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Wealixir being a close-knit team will together work upon to further improvise our Vision &amp; Mission.</p> </div> </div> <div id="hod" class="w3-container searchable-content" style="padding-top: 16px; padding-right: 16px; padding-bottom: 16px; padding-left: 16px;"> <h2 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229); border-bottom-width: 2px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(255, 152, 0);">HOD List</h2> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">At Wealixir, we have capable individuals leading different departments. These Heads of Departments ensure that the company delivers its best performance.</p> <table class="w3-table w3-bordered w3-striped w3-hoverable"> <thead> <tr> <th>Department</th> <th>Head of Department</th> <th>Details</th> <!-- New column for links --> </tr> </thead> <tbody> <tr> <td>CEO</td> <td>Valance Fernandes</td> <td><a target="_blank" href="https://ind.delve.office.com/?u=cb996caa-18dc-436a-b751-f0684ec0ac21&amp;v=profiledetails" class="w3-button w3-blue" style="background-color: rgb(255, 152, 0); color: white; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;">View Details</a></td> </tr> <tr> <td>Partner</td> <td>Santosh Poojari</td> <td><a target="_blank" href="https://m365.cloud.microsoft/search/overview?auth=2&amp;origindomain=microsoft365&amp;pp=7f96e618-a703-4d18-8644-1dbcf66a17e9%408f698e86-8712-49ca-a246-b593f2619807%7Csantosh%40wealixir.com" class="w3-button w3-blue" style="background-color: rgb(255, 152, 0); color: white; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;">View Details</a></td> </tr> <tr> <td>Transactions</td> <td>Khusboo Savla</td> <td><a target="_blank" href="https://m365.cloud.microsoft/search/overview?auth=2&amp;origindomain=microsoft365&amp;pp=5f7d4fa2-89f4-4433-8cb0-a8f4256824f2%408f698e86-8712-49ca-a246-b593f2619807%7Cmf%40wealixir.com" class="w3-button w3-blue" style="background-color: rgb(255, 152, 0); color: white; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;">View Details</a></td> </tr> <tr> <td>Accounts</td> <td>Sayuri Mahadik</td> <td><a target="_blank" href="https://m365.cloud.microsoft/search/overview?auth=2&amp;origindomain=microsoft365&amp;pp=ff0f1cda-3763-495c-9990-c5ca9b85622c%408f698e86-8712-49ca-a246-b593f2619807%7Caccounts%40wealixir.com" class="w3-button w3-blue" style="background-color: rgb(255, 152, 0); color: white; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;">View Details</a></td> </tr> <tr> <td>Accounting &amp; Compliance</td> <td>Nilesh Jha</td> <td><a target="_blank" href="https://app.fireflies.ai/guest-mode/login?meetingId=01JVVS3RE1JX62B2YHB2PBH830" class="w3-button w3-blue" style="background-color: rgb(255, 152, 0); color: white; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;">View Details</a></td> </tr> <tr> <td>Administration</td> <td>Bharat Phalaskar</td> <td><a target="_blank" href="link-to-bharat-phalaskar-details" class="w3-button w3-blue" style="background-color: rgb(255, 152, 0); color: white; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;">View Details</a></td> </tr> <tr> <td>Tech Excutive</td> <td>Jay Jha</td> <td><a target="_blank" href="https://ind.delve.office.com/?u=8bd8a8f1-d2be-4c8d-923d-f4f9e10da962&amp;v=profiledetails" class="w3-button w3-blue" style="background-color: rgb(255, 152, 0); color: white; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;">View Details</a></td> </tr> <tr> <td>Human Resource (HR)</td> <td>Anushka Agrawal</td> <td><a target="_blank" href="https://ind.delve.office.com/?u=d60e986b-fe8f-4929-a1ec-3307f21b421d&amp;v=profiledetails" class="w3-button w3-blue" style="background-color: rgb(255, 152, 0); color: white; margin-top: 10px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px;">View Details</a></td> </tr> </tbody> </table> </div> <div id="org_chart" class="w3-container searchable-content" style="padding: 16px;"> <h2 style=" font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229); border-bottom: 2px solid rgb(255, 152, 0); "> Organization Chart </h2> <img src="https://ik.imagekit.io/4kztyt3ky/image%20(2).png?updatedAt=1763032321650" alt="Organization Chart" style="width: 120%; max-width: 1000px; margin-top: 16px; border-radius: 8px;"> </div> <div id="band_structure" class="w3-container searchable-content" style="padding: 16px;"> <h2 style=" font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229); border-bottom: 2px solid rgb(255,152,0); "> Company Band Structure </h2> <img src="https://ik.imagekit.io/4kztyt3ky/image%20(3).png?updatedAt=1763032488014" alt="Company Band Structure" style="width: 100%; max-width: 1000px; margin-top: 16px; border-radius: 8px;"> </div> <div id="time_attendance" class="w3-container searchable-content" style="padding-top: 16px; padding-right: 16px; padding-bottom: 16px; padding-left: 16px;"> <h2 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229); border-bottom-width: 2px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(255, 152, 0);">Work Timings</h2> <h4 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;"><strong>Department-wise Timings</strong></h4> <ul> <li><strong>Insurance &amp; Investment Dept:</strong> 9:00 am – 5:30 pm (Mon–Sat)<br /><em>Closed on 2nd &amp; 4th Saturdays</em></li> <li><strong>Tax Dept:</strong> 10:00 am onwards (Mon–Sat)<br /><em>Closed on 4th Saturdays</em></li> <li><strong>Other Departments:</strong> Follow Insurance &amp; Investment Dept timings unless informed otherwise.</li> </ul> <!-- Late coming policy (HTML) --> <section class="late-coming-policy" aria-labelledby="late-coming-title"> <style> .late-coming-policy { font-family: Montserrat, Arial, sans-serif; max-width: 720px; } .policy-title { color: #1e88e5; margin-bottom: 0.25rem; } .policy-sub { font-weight: 600; margin-top: 0.25rem; } .policy-list { margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 1.25rem; } </style> <h3 id="late-coming-title" class="policy-title">Late Coming Rule</h3> <p class="policy-sub">General rule</p> <ul class="policy-list"> <li>Report before <strong>9:30 AM</strong>.</li> <li>If an employee arrives after <strong>9:30 AM</strong>, up to <strong>5</strong> such late arrivals are allowed per month without deduction.</li> <li>From the <strong>6th</strong> late arrival in the same month onward, a <strong>half-day (½ day) leave</strong> will be deducted for every late occurrence.</li> </ul> </section> </div> <div id="leave_policy" class="w3-container searchable-content" style="padding:16px;"> <h2 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color:#1e88e5; border-bottom:2px solid #ff9800;"> Leave Policy – 2026 </h2> <h3 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color:#1e88e5;">Public Holidays – 2026</h3> <table class="w3-table w3-bordered w3-striped w3-hoverable"> <thead> <tr> <th>Date</th> <th>Day</th> <th>Holiday</th> <th>Comments</th> <th>WCG Leaves</th> <th>Comments / Adjustments</th> </tr> </thead> <tbody> <tr> <td>01 Jan 2026</td> <td>Thursday</td> <td>New Year</td> <td>Full Day Off</td> <td>Yes</td> <td></td> </tr> <tr> <td>26 Jan 2026</td> <td>Monday</td> <td>Republic Day</td> <td>Full Day Off</td> <td>Yes</td> <td></td> </tr> <tr> <td>03 Mar 2026</td> <td>Tuesday</td> <td>Holi</td> <td>Full Day Off</td> <td>Yes</td> <td></td> </tr> <tr> <td>27 Mar 2026</td> <td>Friday</td> <td>Ram Navami</td> <td>Full Day Off</td> <td>Yes</td> <td></td> </tr> <tr> <td>03 Apr 2026</td> <td>Friday</td> <td>Good Friday</td> <td>Full Day Off</td> <td>Yes</td> <td>Sat 04 Apr Holiday · Sat 11 Apr Working</td> </tr> <tr> <td>01 May 2026</td> <td>Friday</td> <td>Maharashtra Day</td> <td>Full Day Off</td> <td>Yes</td> <td></td> </tr> <tr> <td>15 Aug 2026</td> <td>Saturday</td> <td>Independence Day</td> <td>Full Day Off</td> <td>Yes</td> <td></td> </tr> <tr> <td>14 Sep 2026</td> <td>Monday</td> <td>Ganesh Chaturthi</td> <td>Full Day Off</td> <td>Yes</td> <td></td> </tr> <tr> <td>02 Oct 2026</td> <td>Friday</td> <td>Mahatma Gandhi Jayanti</td> <td>Full Day Off</td> <td>Yes</td> <td>Sat 03 Oct Holiday · Sat 10 Oct Working</td> </tr> <tr> <td>20 Oct 2026</td> <td>Tuesday</td> <td>Dasara</td> <td>Full Day Off</td> <td>Yes</td> <td></td> </tr> <tr> <td>10 Nov 2026</td> <td>Tuesday</td> <td>Diwali – Balipratipada</td> <td>Full Day Off</td> <td>Yes</td> <td>Sat 07 Nov Holiday · Sat 14 Nov Working</td> </tr> <tr> <td>25 Dec 2026</td> <td>Friday</td> <td>Christmas</td> <td>Full Day Off</td> <td>Yes</td> <td></td> </tr> </tbody> </table> </div> </table> <h3 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229);">Casual Leaves</h3> <ul> <li>Permanent employees are eligible for <strong>20 casual leaves per year</strong>, subject to Reporting Manager’s approval. <br> <strong>Carry Forward:</strong> Up to <strong>5 unused leaves</strong> may be carried forward to the next leave cycle. <br> Once the yearly leave balance is fully utilized, employees may avail up to <strong>5 unpaid leaves</strong>. <br> In special circumstances such as <strong>medical emergencies or marriage</strong>, employees may avail up to <strong>20 additional unpaid leaves</strong>. <br> If the employee does not return to work after exhausting the above leave limits, the management reserves the right to <strong>take necessary action, including termination</strong>. </li> <li><strong>Probationary Employees:</strong> During the probation period, employees are eligible for <strong>1 leave per month</strong> (i.e., 6 leaves for a 6-month probation). If the probation period is extended to 9 months, the leave entitlement will be <strong>9 leaves</strong> accordingly. <br> After confirmation, <strong>1.5 leaves per month</strong> will accrue up to the financial year end (March). <br> Please note: <strong>1.5 leaves per month will only begin after confirmation</strong>, not during the probation period.</li> <li><strong>No encashment</strong> of leaves under any circumstances.</li> <li><strong>Planned leave:</strong> Apply early to help managers plan resources efficiently.</li> </ul> <h3 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229);">Process to Apply for Leaves</h3> <ul> <li> Login on the <strong><a href="https://wealixir.sharepoint.com/sites/SupportTickets/Lists/WFH%20Requests/Leave_Calendar.aspx?viewid=25983205-c54b-4dbf-a84f685d1d53" target="_blank">Leave Request Portal</a></strong> and apply for <strong>WFH, Leaves, Half Days, Client Visits, or Agency Visits</strong>, etc. </li> <li> <strong>Only in case of emergency or special situations</strong>, leaves should be applied through email to your Reporting Manager and keep HR in CC. </li> <li> <strong>Unapproved leaves</strong> will be treated as <strong>double leave deduction</strong>. </li> </ul> <h3 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229);">Birthday / Anniversary Leave</h3> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Each employee is eligible for <strong>1 special leave</strong> on their birthday or marriage anniversary. Apply in advance.</p> <h3 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229);">Comp Off</h3> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">If you work on a Sunday or public holiday, your manager must inform HR for comp off to be credited.</p> </div> <div id="loan_policy" class="w3-container searchable-content" style="padding:16px; margin-left: 250px;"> <h2 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229); border-bottom:2px solid rgb(255, 152, 0);"> Loan Policy </h2> <table class="w3-table w3-bordered w3-striped w3-hoverable"> <thead> <tr> <th>Tenure of Employment</th> <th>Amount</th> <th>Repayment</th> <th>Interest</th> </tr> </thead> <tbody> <tr> <td>0 – 6 Months</td> <td>Not Eligible</td> <td>Not Applicable</td> <td>No</td> </tr> <tr> <td>6 – 12 Months</td> <td>CTC / 24</td> <td>Next salary cycle</td> <td>No</td> </tr> <tr> <td>12 – 36 Months</td> <td>CTC / 12</td> <td>Next salary cycle</td> <td>No</td> </tr> <tr> <td>36 – 60 Months</td> <td>CTC / 12</td> <td>Next three salary cycles</td> <td>No</td> </tr> <tr> <td>Above 60 Months</td> <td>CTC / 4 or Gratuity</td> <td>Next three salary cycles / Up to 12 Months</td> <td>No / Yes</td> </tr> </tbody> </table> <br> <!-- Advance Salary Policy --> <h3 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229);"> Advance Salary Policy </h3> <p> The Company may, at its sole discretion, provide an <strong>Advance Salary</strong> to eligible employees, subject to the terms and conditions outlined below. </p> <h4>1. Eligibility</h4> <ul> <li>The employee must have successfully completed the probation period.</li> <li>The employee must not be serving a notice period at the time of application.</li> </ul> <h4>2. Repayment Timeline</h4> <p> Any advance salary availed shall be recovered in full from the <strong>immediately succeeding salary cycle</strong>. </p> <p> <em>Illustration:</em> If an advance salary is taken on <strong>20 January</strong>, the amount shall be deducted from the salary processed on <strong>1 February</strong>. </p> <h4>3. Maximum Permissible Amount</h4> <p> An employee may avail an advance salary in addition to any existing long-term loan, provided that the <strong>total monthly deductions</strong> (including loan EMI and advance salary recovery) do not exceed <strong>50% of the employee’s monthly in-hand salary</strong>. </p> <p> <em>Illustration:</em><br> If an employee’s monthly in-hand salary is INR 20,000 and an existing loan deduction of INR 5,000 is already in place, the maximum permissible advance salary would be INR 5,000, ensuring that total deductions do not exceed INR 10,000 (50%). </p> <h4>4. Cooling-Off Period</h4> <p> A minimum cooling-off period of <strong>three (3) months</strong> shall apply between two advance salary requests. Employees may apply for a new advance salary only after completion of this period from the date of the previous advance. </p> <h4>5. Application Process</h4> <p> Employees seeking an advance salary must submit a formal request via email to the <strong>Human Resources (HR)</strong> department, clearly mentioning: </p> <ul> <li>The amount of advance salary requested</li> <li>The reason for requesting the advance</li> <li>Details of any existing loans and ongoing monthly deductions, if applicable</li> </ul> <p> All requests shall be reviewed by HR and are subject to management approval. </p> <h4>6. General Conditions</h4> <ul> <li>Grant of advance salary is subject to management discretion and internal approval processes.</li> <li> The Company reserves the right to amend, modify, suspend, or withdraw this policy at any time without prior notice. </li> </ul> </div> <div id="incentive_policy" class="w3-container searchable-content" style="padding:16px; margin-left: 250px;"> <h2 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229); border-bottom-width: 2px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(255, 152, 0);">Incentive Structure</h2> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">All Figures are for 1L of Investment / Premium / Billing</p> <table class="w3-table w3-bordered w3-striped w3-hoverable"> <thead> <tr> <th>Category</th> <th>Sub Type</th> <th>Incentive</th> <th>Credit for MDRT</th> </tr> </thead> <tbody> <!-- Life --> <tr> <td rowspan="2">Life</td> <td>Non-Single</td> <td>11,600</td> <td>100,000</td> </tr> <tr> <td>Single</td> <td>660</td> <td>5,000</td> </tr> <!-- General --> <tr> <td rowspan="8">General</td> <td>Health / PA - 1 Year</td> <td>8,500</td> <td>100,000</td> </tr> <tr> <td>Health / PA - 2 Year</td> <td>4,250</td> <td>62,500</td> </tr> <tr> <td>Health / PA - 3 Year</td> <td>2,833</td> <td>75,000</td> </tr> <tr> <td>Health (Port)</td> <td>5,000</td> <td>50,000</td> </tr> <tr> <td>Travel</td> <td>5,000</td> <td>5,000</td> </tr> <tr> <td>Motor</td> <td>8,500</td> <td>50,000</td> </tr> <tr> <td>Others</td> <td>5,000</td> <td>50,000</td> </tr> <tr> <td>Upsell</td> <td>5,000</td> <td>50,000</td> </tr> <!-- Mutual Funds --> <tr> <td>Mutual Funds</td> <td>Lumpsum</td> <td>250</td> <td>2,500</td> </tr> <!-- PMS --> <tr> <td>PMS</td> <td>SIP</td> <td>5,000</td> <td>50,000</td> </tr> <!-- Fixed Deposits --> <tr> <td rowspan="2">Fixed Deposits</td> <td>One time</td> <td>330</td> <td>5,000</td> </tr> <tr> <td>FD to Depend on Tenure</td> <td colspan="2"></td> </tr> <!-- Tax --> <tr> <td rowspan="2">Tax</td> <td>Per ITR</td> <td>500</td> <td>5,000</td> </tr> <tr> <td>Other Items</td> <td>5,000</td> <td>50,000</td> </tr> </tbody> </table> <h3 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229);">Incentive Levels and Bonus Structure</h3> <table class="w3-table w3-bordered w3-striped w3-hoverable"> <thead> <tr> <th>Levels</th> <th>Target</th> <th>Extra Bonus</th> </tr> </thead> <tbody> <tr> <td>Half MDRT</td> <td>2,000,000</td> <td>25,000</td> </tr> <tr> <td>MDRT</td> <td>4,000,000</td> <td>30,000</td> </tr> <tr> <td>1.5 MDRT</td> <td>6,000,000</td> <td>37,500</td> </tr> <tr> <td>2 MDRT</td> <td>8,000,000</td> <td>50,000</td> </tr> </tbody> </table> </div> <div class="w3-main"> <div id="joining" class="w3-container searchable-content" style="padding:16px; margin-left: 250px;"> <h2 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229); border-bottom-width: 2px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(255, 152, 0);">HR Policies</h2> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">The below are the HR policies for <strong>Wealixir</strong> Henceforth known as the <strong> COMPANY.</strong></p> <h3 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: #1E88E5;"> Onboarding Process </h3> <div style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; line-height:1.8;"> <h4 style="color:#1E88E5; margin-top:20px;">1. Full-Time Employees</h4> <ul> <li>Application/Referral received</li> <li>Aptitude Test is conducted (mandatory)</li> <li>Interview with Reporting Manager / HOD</li> <li>HR shares Google Form to collect personal and bank details</li> <li>Reporting Manager submits Software Access Form to IT</li> <li>Razorpay account is created by HR</li> <li>Employee uploads required documents</li> <li>IT creates: <ul> <li>Jamku Login ID</li> <li>Official Email ID</li> <li>Software / System Access as requested by Manager</li> </ul> </li> <li>ID Card details are shared with Vendor for printing</li> </ul> <h4 style="color:#1E88E5; margin-top:20px;">2. Interns</h4> <ul> <li>Aptitude Test is conducted (mandatory)</li> <li>Interview with HR and Reporting Manager</li> <li>HR collects personal details via Google Form</li> <li>Reporting Manager submits Software Access Form</li> <li>Razorpay account created (if required)</li> <li>IT creates Jamku ID, Email ID and provides required software access</li> <li>ID Card issued only if needed</li> </ul> <h4 style="color:#1E88E5; margin-top:20px;">3. Contractors</h4> <ul> <li>HR receives confirmation of engagement</li> <li>HR collects required personal details</li> <li>Razorpay account created (if required)</li> <li>Software access, Email ID and ID Card are provided only if approved based on project requirement</li> </ul> </div> </table> <h3 id="rules" style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229);">Ground Rules</h3> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">At Wealixir, we believe in complete transparency, integrity &amp; compassion towards work. There is a certain code of conduct which we expect our employees to follow, which creates a professional culture helping us to be a little unique and different amongst this demanding industry.</p> <ul style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;"> <li><strong>Phone calls not being answered:</strong> In case while you’re trying to connect to some client or colleague and the call is unanswered, kindly send an SMS or a WhatsApp message to that person stating the reason for your call. If you cannot attend calls, similarly drop a message that you will get back shortly. This helps in maintaining good follow-up and accountability.</li> <li><strong>Use SURNAME first:</strong> While compiling or presenting any data where the names of clients or colleagues are involved, always use the SURNAME first followed by the FIRST name.</li> <li><strong>Reverting to client emails:</strong> Kindly revert to the mail received from the client in one line stating, “We acknowledge the receipt of your mail and will get back to you in a day or two.”</li> <li><strong>Don’t assume a response:</strong> If you are busy or on a call, drop a message stating what work you had or the reason for your call, rather than assuming the person will revert back.</li> <li><strong>AVO – AVOID VERBAL ORDER:</strong> A very important practice is to ensure that all communication happens in written mode, i.e., via emails or WhatsApp (if urgent). Verbal orders should be avoided.</li> <li><strong>EXCEL SHEET:</strong> When creating an Excel sheet, always FREEZE the 1st row/Title row for easy understanding and to ensure it looks presentable and uniform. Avoid figures in decimal form and always total at the end.</li> <li><strong>UNHAPPY CLIENT:</strong> If you encounter an unhappy or unsatisfied client/customer, report it to Management immediately before the client approaches them.</li> <li><strong>MEETING RECORDINGS:</strong> If you miss any meetings (MM, TT, etc.) and listen to the recording later, kindly notify everyone on the Team Shree WhatsApp group as an update to keep everyone informed.</li> </ul> <h3 id="probation_policy" style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229);">Probation Policy</h3> <ul> <li>After <span>6 months of probation,</span> employee to have a meeting with <Span>Manager and HR </Span> about the performance and Manager and HR to decide on the confirmation or extension.</li> <li>Post 6 months, the employee needs to set up a meeting/call with the manager to understand their status and check if they are being confirmed or need an extension. The result for which will be conveyed through email.</li> <li>The employee’s appointment will be confirmed in writing on successful completion of the said probationary period. <span>It may get extended by further period of 3 months if employee’s performance is not found satisfactory.</span></li> <li>Post 3 months of extension, still if the employee’s performance is not up to the mark his/her employment will be terminated.</li> <li>If no confirmation is made in writing at the end of the probationary period, it will be deemed to have been extended until the company confirms you in writing.</li> <li>During the probation &amp; thereafter confirmation, it is mandatory to attend all the training assigned to the employee.</li> </ul> <div id="personal_relationship" style="padding-top: 16px; padding-right: 16px; padding-bottom: 16px; padding-left: 16px;"> <h3 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229);">Personal Relationships in the Workplace Policy</h3> <h3 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229);">Purpose</h3> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">The purpose of this policy is to establish clear, transparent, and inclusive guidelines for managing personal relationships in the workplace. While the organization respects employees' privacy, romantic relationships at work can lead to conflicts of interest, favouritism, disruption, or misconduct if not appropriately managed.</p> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">This policy aims to:</p> <ul> <li>Promote transparency through responsible disclosure of romantic relationships.</li> <li>Prevent undue advantage, bias, or abuse of authority.</li> <li>Maintain a professional, respectful, and collaborative environment.</li> <li>Prevent negative impact on team morale or workplace integrity.</li> <li>Reduce disputes escalating under the Prevention of Sexual Harassment (POSH) framework.</li> <li>Deter misuse of POSH provisions for personal conflicts or grievances.</li> </ul> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">This policy applies to all romantic or intimate relationships, including dating, marriage, extra-marital affairs, same-sex relationships, and any emotional involvement between employees.</p> <h3 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229);">Scope</h3> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">This policy applies to all employees across departments, roles, and locations, including full-time, part-time, consultants, contractors, and interns.</p> <h3 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229);">Policy Guidelines</h3> <h4 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">Mandatory Disclosure</h4> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Employees engaged in romantic relationships must disclose it in writing to HR and sign the Declaration form.</p> <h4 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">Failure to Disclose</h4> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Non-disclosure leading to conflict of interest, disruption, or reputational harm may result in disciplinary action, including termination.</p> <h4 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">Organizational Structuring</h4> <ul> <li>No reporting or manager-subordinate relationship between individuals in a relationship.</li> <li>They cannot be in the same vertical/reporting structure.</li> <li>They may work together only as peers with no mutual appraisal or feedback.</li> </ul> <h4 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">Performance Evaluations</h4> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Employees in relationships cannot evaluate, appraise, or provide feedback on each other's work.</p> <h4 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">Professional Conduct</h4> <ul> <li>Personal conflicts should not affect workplace dynamics.</li> <li>Public displays of affection (PDA) are strictly prohibited, including during events and offsites.</li> <li>Professionalism must be maintained at all times.</li> </ul> <h4 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">Post-Relationship Conduct</h4> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">In case of a breakup, professionalism must continue. POSH complaints are valid only if they meet legal definitions of misconduct or harassment.</p> <h4 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">Conflict of Interest</h4> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">HR may restructure teams if there's evidence of favouritism, bias, team discomfort, or productivity impact.</p> <h4 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">Applicability During Events, Travel &amp; Offsites</h4> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">All guidelines apply during office travel, offsites, events, or external engagements.</p> <h4 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">HR Discretion</h4> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">HR and Management may take necessary actions, including reassignments or termination, based on specific situations.</p> <h4 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">Married Individuals and Workplace Conduct</h4> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">All relationships must be disclosed, including extra-marital or same-sex. The company does not interfere in personal matters but maintains professional boundaries and structures within the workplace.</p> <h4 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">Undisclosed Relationships &amp; Complaints</h4> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Undisclosed relationships affecting work may lead to disciplinary action. The company may notify impacted stakeholders if necessary but does not intervene in personal legal disputes unless required by law.</p> <h4 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">Confidentiality</h4> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">All disclosures are confidential and shared only on a need-to-know basis.</p> <h4 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">Consequences of Violation</h4> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Violations can lead to formal warnings, role restructuring, suspension, or termination if workplace disruption occurs.</p> <h4 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">Other Provisions</h4> <ul> <li>Cooling-Off Period: Post-breakup, reassignments may be made for 3–6 months to minimize interactions.</li> <li>Policy Review: Employees will acknowledge understanding this policy at onboarding.</li> <li>Both parties must sign the declaration form upon disclosure.</li> </ul> <h3 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229);">Employee Declaration</h3> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">I, [Employee Full Name], working as [Designation] in [Department/Team] at VNG/Wealixir Consulting, confirm that:</p> <ul> <li>I have read and understood the Personal Relationships in the Workplace Policy.</li> <li>I agree to mandatory disclosure and maintaining professional boundaries.</li> <li>I understand the consequences of non-compliance.</li> </ul> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Current Status:</p> <ul> <li>☐ I am not involved in any personal relationship with another employee.</li> <li>☐ I am in a personal relationship with an employee and have disclosed it to HR. (Details below)</li> </ul> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Employee Signature: _______________________</p> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Employee Name: __________________________</p> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Employee ID: _____________________________</p> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Date: ____________________________________</p> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">HR Representative (Witness/Verifier): __________________________</p> <h4 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">If in a personal relationship, fill details:</h4> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Name of Second Party Employee: ______________________</p> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Employee Vertical/Department: ______________________</p> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Employee Designation: ___________________________</p> <a href="https://forms.office.com/r/qB1KQLvEQK?origin=lprLink" target="_blank"><button style="padding: 10px 20px; background-color: #0078D4; color: white; border: none; border-radius: 5px; cursor: pointer;">Fill Declaration Form</button></a> </div> <div id="POSH_POLICY" style="padding-top: 16px; padding-right: 16px; padding-bottom: 16px; padding-left: 16px;"> <h3 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229);">Prevention of Sexual Harassment (POSH) Policy</h3> <h4 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">1. Objective</h4> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Wealixir Consulting Pvt. Ltd. is committed to providing a safe, dignified, and harassment-free workplace for all employees, irrespective of gender or role. This policy is aligned with the Sexual Harassment of Women at Workplace (Prevention, Prohibition and Redressal) Act, 2013 ("POSH Act").</p> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">The policy aims to:</p> <ul> <li>Prevent sexual harassment at the workplace</li> <li>Provide a structured redressal mechanism</li> <li>Foster a safe, inclusive, and respectful environment for all</li> </ul> <h4 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">2. Scope</h4> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">This policy applies to all employees—full-time, part-time, interns, freelancers, consultants, and contractors—across all genders, roles, and locations including:</p> <ul> <li>Office premises</li> <li>Virtual workspaces</li> <li>Work-related travel, offsites, and client locations</li> <li>Any place visited during the course of employment</li> </ul> <h4 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">3. Definitions</h4> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;"><strong>Aggrieved Woman:</strong> Any woman alleging sexual harassment at the workplace.</p> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;"><strong>Sexual Harassment includes (but is not limited to):</strong></p> <ul> <li>Unwelcome physical contact, advances, or invading personal space</li> <li>Requests for sexual favors, implicitly or explicitly</li> <li>Sexually colored remarks or jokes</li> <li>Sharing or showing explicit content</li> <li>Inappropriate messages via email, social media, or calls</li> <li>Staring, suggestive gestures, or comments on appearance</li> <li>Romantic propositions despite disinterest</li> <li>Misconduct during office events or offsites</li> <li>Any act creating a hostile work environment</li> </ul> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;"><strong>Not considered Sexual Harassment:</strong> Consensual relationships without misuse of authority, respectful compliments, and constructive feedback.</p> <h4 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">4. Internal Committee (IC)</h4> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Formed as per the POSH Act, comprising:</p> <ul> <li>Presiding Officer: Mrs. Prachi Mohite</li> <li>Employee Member: Ms. Anushka Agrawal (HR)</li> <li>External Member: Angelica Dsouza</li> </ul> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Contact: <a href="mailto:hr@wealixir.com">hr@wealixir.com</a></p> <h4 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">5. Filing a Complaint</h4> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Complaints can be filed by the aggrieved employee, or through a friend, colleague, or witness. Complaints must be in writing and filed within 3 months of the incident (extendable in certain cases).</p> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;"><strong>IC Responsibilities:</strong></p> <ul> <li>Acknowledge within 7 days</li> <li>Initiate inquiry within 10 days</li> <li>Complete inquiry within 90 days</li> <li>Submit findings to the employer</li> </ul> <h4 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">6. Redressal Process</h4> <ul> <li>Confidential and impartial inquiry</li> <li>Both parties have the right to present their case</li> <li>Action may include warnings, suspension, termination, or other remedies</li> <li>Strict no-retaliation policy for complainants and witnesses</li> </ul> <h4 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">7. False or Malicious Complaints</h4> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">False complaints made with malicious intent are punishable. However, inability to prove a complaint does not attract punishment unless malicious intent is evident.</p> <h4 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">8. Confidentiality</h4> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">All proceedings and information under this policy will remain strictly confidential. Breach of confidentiality by any party will result in disciplinary action.</p> <h4 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">9. Employer’s Responsibilities</h4> <ul> <li>Conduct POSH awareness and training sessions</li> <li>Display the POSH policy prominently</li> <li>Support the IC in all proceedings</li> <li>Submit annual compliance reports as per law</li> <li>Ensure protection against victimization</li> </ul> <h4 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">10. Non-Retaliation</h4> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">No employee will face adverse consequences for filing a genuine complaint or participating in an inquiry. Any proven retaliation will lead to strict disciplinary action, up to termination.</p> <h4 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">11. Our Commitment</h4> <ul> <li>Zero tolerance for harassment</li> <li>Equal opportunities for all</li> <li>Respect for personal dignity</li> <li>A safe and inclusive workplace</li> </ul> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;"><strong>Date of Policy Implementation:</strong> [Insert Date]</p> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;"><strong>Next Review Date:</strong> [Insert Date]</p> <h4 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">Employee Declaration</h4> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">I, ____________________________ (Employee Name), confirm that I have read, understood, and agree to comply with the Prevention of Sexual Harassment (POSH) Policy of Wealixir Consulting Pvt. Ltd. I commit to upholding dignity, respect, and professionalism in the workplace.</p> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Employee Signature: _____________________ &nbsp;&nbsp; Date: _______________</p> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Employee ID / Department: ____________________________</p> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Witness / HR Representative: ____________________________</p> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">For any queries or concerns, please contact: <a href="mailto:hr@wealixir.com">hr@wealixir.com</a></p> </div> <h3 id="controlled_substances" style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229);">Controlled Substances in Workplace</h3> <ul> <li>Employees who engage in the unlawful sale, distribution, or attempted sale, possession or purchase of controlled substances while at the workplace, or while performing in a work related capacity, will be subject to criminal, civil and disciplinary penalties.</li> <li>Such illegal acts, even if engaged in off duty, may result in disciplinary action.</li> <li>No employee shall use alcohol or illegal or illicit substances at the worksite.</li> <li>An employee may be required to undergo a confidential medical examination to ascertain the cause of impairment or disability when there exists a “reasonable suspicion” based on specific, reliable observations that such impairment or disability is a result of the use of alcohol or a controlled substance.</li> <li>If alcohol or controlled substance use or impairment is found to exist, <strong>The Company would </strong> determine the appropriate course of action which may include disciplinary action.</li> </ul> <h3 id="gift" style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229);">Gifts</h3> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">You are not permitted to give/receive any unauthorized gifts to/ from clients. Advance approval from management is required before you accept or solicit a gift of any kind from a client. In case, if you receive the gifts from clients please be informed to Mr.Valance Fernandes and / Mr.Santosh Poojari about the same.</p> <h3 id="social_media" style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229);">Social Media Policy</h3> <ul style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; line-height:1.8;"> <li>The Company encourages positive social media engagement and supports employees in sharing the organization’s work, achievements, and updates.</li> <li>Employees are expected to <strong>like, share, and positively engage</strong> with official Company posts on <strong>LinkedIn, Instagram, YouTube</strong>, and other approved platforms whenever such communication is shared by the Company.</li> <li>Employees may also be requested to <strong>post Company updates as their WhatsApp Status</strong> during campaigns, events, achievements, or brand-building activities. Cooperation and timely participation are expected.</li> </ul> <h3 id="public_statements" style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229);">Public Statements</h3> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">All media inquiries regarding the company and its operations must be referred to the Directors or Partners of the firm. Only the Director or the Partner is authorized to make or approve public statement s pertaining to the company or its operations.</p> <h3 id="company_property" style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229);">Company Property</h3> <ul> <li><strong>The Company </strong> reserves the right to have access and to inspect all Company provided properties (desks, files, offices, vehicles, etc.), and any packages, bags, briefcases, handbags, or other containers entering or leaving the <strong>Company’s</strong> premises.</li> <li>Any search of Company Properties, Facilities or vehicles does not have to be based on reasonable suspicion. For your protection and safety, Employees are not permitted to enter the office or any other work are as at any time they are not scheduled to work, unless otherwise approved by Management.</li> <li>Employees are required to ensure the safe keeping of any company property assigned to them. No employees allowed taking any company property (including laptop &amp; mobiles) outside the company premises without written communication of management.</li> </ul> <h3 id="workplace_monitoring" style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229);">Workplace Monitoring</h3> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;"><strong>The Company </strong> may conduct work place monitoring for a variety of reasons, including, but not limited to, quality control, Staff Member safety, security, efficient performance, and client satisfaction. Messages sent through the <strong>Company’s</strong> network may be retrieved and/or reviewed by the Company as necessary.</p> <div id="other_policies" class="w3-container searchable-content" style="padding-top: 16px; padding-right: 16px; padding-bottom: 16px; padding-left: 16px;"> <h2 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229); border-bottom-width: 2px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(255, 152, 0);">Other Policies</h2> <h3 id="information_security_policy" style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229);">Information Security Policy</h3> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;"></p> <ul> <li>Not to use the information obtained in the conduct of The Company’s business for personal or business or any other advantages.</li> <li>Unauthorized disclosure of confidential information or records of The Company or its clients.</li> </ul> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;"></p> <h3 id="misconduct_policy" style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229);">Misconduct Policy</h3> <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;"><strong>The Company </strong> would take strict action on following misconduct activities:</p> <ul> <li>Falsifying records or giving false information to the management or employees responsible for record keeping.</li> <li>Failure to provide accurate &amp; complete information whenever such information is required by an authorized person.</li> <li>Failure to comply with health, safety and sanitation requirements, rules and regulations.</li> <li>Negligence in performance of assigned duties.</li> <li>Possible criminal action, verbal mistreatment of colleagues, an ongoing failure to follow supervisory instructions, tardiness or poor attendance, major violations of rules (possession of or the using of alcoholic beverages or controlled substances during working hours), inappropriate use of The Company’s property, equipment or facilities, fighting or violating safety rules including failure to report an accident involving The Company’s vehicles or equipment, insubordination, stealing, falsifying a time sheet or any official document, accepting a tip, gift, or bribe offered by a contractor or entity that may contract with The Company assign of appreciation for performance of your required duties; and committing other serious illegal acts.</li> <li>Insubordination, including disobedience, or failure or refusal to carry out assignments or instructions.</li> <li>Loafing, loitering, sleeping or engaging in unauthorized personal business.</li> </ul> </div> <h3 id="salary_policy" style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">Salary Policy</h3> <p>Employee's salary would be credited to his/her account on or before the 7th day of consecutive month.</p> <h3 id="Maternity_benefits" style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;"> Maternity Benefits </h3> <p> Women employees are entitled to maternity benefits in accordance with the <strong>labour laws of India</strong>. The eligibility criteria and benefit details are outlined below. </p> <h4>Basic Entitlement and Eligibility</h4> <p> Eligible women employees are entitled to <strong>up to 26 weeks of paid maternity leave</strong> for the <strong>first two surviving children</strong>. For the <strong>third child and onwards</strong>, the maternity leave entitlement shall be <strong>12 weeks</strong>. </p> <p> To qualify for maternity benefits, the employee must have completed <strong>at least 80 days of service</strong> with the same employer during the <strong>12 months immediately preceding the expected date of delivery</strong>. </p> <h4>Utilization of Maternity Leave</h4> <p> Out of the 26 weeks of maternity leave, up to <strong>8 weeks</strong> may be availed before the expected date of delivery, with the remaining period to be taken after childbirth. In cases where the entitlement is 12 weeks (third child onwards), up to <strong>6 weeks</strong> may be availed prior to delivery. </p> <p> During the maternity leave period, the employee shall receive maternity benefits <strong>equivalent to her average daily wages</strong> for the actual period of absence. Accordingly, maternity leave shall be treated as <strong>fully paid leave</strong>. </p> <h4>Other Situations Covered</h4> <p> Adoptive mothers who adopt a child below the age of <strong>three months</strong> and commissioning mothers through <strong>surrogacy</strong> are entitled to <strong>12 weeks of paid maternity leave</strong> from the date the child is handed over. </p> <p> In the event of a <strong>miscarriage or medical termination of pregnancy</strong>, the employee is entitled to <strong>6 weeks of paid leave</strong>. An additional leave of up to <strong>one month</strong> may be granted in cases of pregnancy-related illness or medical complications, subject to medical certification. </p> <h3 id="personal_communication_policy" style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">Personal Communication Policy</h3> <p> <strong>PHONE CALLS</strong><br /> It is acknowledged that personal communication is inevitable and sometimes necessary. It is expected this will be kept to an appropriate or reasonable level.<br /><br /><strong>EMAIL</strong><br /> The Company provides email addresses to some employees who need them for their jobs. These email addresses are not permitted for personal use, unofficial downloads, copying, etc. The Company has the right to access the system to determine whether private use is excessive or inappropriate. Email has legal status as a document and is accepted as evidence in a court of law. The Company can be held responsible for the contents of email messages, including any attachments, etc. Access to emails can be demanded as part of legal action in some circumstances.<br /> Attending to and acknowledging emails in the absence from work should be diligently followed. This is one step towards being professional and responsible.<br /><br /><strong>INTERNET</strong><br /> The internet is a facility provided by The Company for business use. Management has the right to access the system to determine whether private use is excessive or inappropriate. The Company’s internet access is not permitted for personal use, unofficial downloads, copying, etc., and any employee caught doing any such inappropriate act would be held personally responsible for the same.<br /> Failure to comply with these instructions is a disciplinary offence and will be subject to appropriate investigation. In serious cases, the penalty for an offence or repetition of an offence may lead to the dismissal of the employee. Staff needs to be continually aware that some forms of internet conduct may also be open to criminal prosecution. </p> <h3 id="Gratuity" style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;"> Gratuity </h3> <p> Gratuity is payable to eligible employees in accordance with the provisions of the <strong>Payment of Gratuity Act, 1972</strong>, wherever applicable. The gratuity amount is calculated based on the employee’s last drawn salary and completed years of service. </p> <h4>Gratuity Formula (Employees Covered under the Payment of Gratuity Act, 1972)</h4> <p> <strong>Gratuity = (Last Drawn Salary × 15 / 26) × Number of Years of Service</strong> </p> <p> <strong>Last Drawn Salary:</strong> Includes Basic Salary plus Dearness Allowance (if applicable). </p> <p> <strong>Number of Years of Service:</strong> Service of six months or more is rounded up to the next full year. Service of less than six months is ignored. </p> <p> <strong>Example:</strong><br> If an employee’s last drawn salary is ₹75,000 and the employee has completed 8 years and 7 months of service (rounded to 9 years), the gratuity payable would be: </p> <p> <strong>₹75,000 × 15 / 26 × 9 ≈ ₹3,89,423</strong> </p> <h4>Gratuity Formula (Employees Not Covered under the Gratuity Act)</h4> <p> <strong>Gratuity = (Last Drawn Salary × 15 / 30) × Number of Years of Service</strong> </p> <p> In such cases, the components of <strong>Last Drawn Salary</strong> and the calculation of <strong>Years of Service</strong> remain the same as described above. </p> <h4>Important Note</h4> <p> Gratuity amounts are <strong>auto-calculated in Razorpay</strong> for employees. The final computation and verification of gratuity figures will be carried out by the Company during <strong>March / April 2026</strong>. </p> <p> Please note that individual gratuity figures cannot be shared prior to the final calculation and confirmation by the concerned team. </p> <!-- <h3 id="phone_calls">Phone Calls</h3> <p>...</p> <h3 id="email">Email</h3> <p>...</p> <h3 id="internet">Internet</h3> <p>...</p> --> <h3 id="dismissal_of_employment" style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">Dismissal of Employment without Severance Pay</h3> <p>The employee who commits one of the following offences shall be punished with termination of employment without severance pay:</p> <ul> <li>Performing duties dishonestly or intentionally committing a criminal offence against the company.</li> <li>Intentionally causing serious damage to the company, or causing serious damage to the company as a result of negligence or carelessness.</li> <li>Violating regulations or rules concerning work or lawful orders of the company after written notice has been given by the Company. In this regard, such written notice shall be valid for 1 year. Except in severe cases, the Company is not required to give a warning.</li> <li>Leaving his/her duty without justifiable reason for 7 consecutive days, regardless of whether there is a holiday in between or not.</li> <li>Being imprisoned by a final judgment. If the imprisonment is for offences committed by negligence or a petty offense, it shall be considered an offense causing damage to the company.</li> </ul> <p></p> <h3 id="employment_termination_resignation" style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">Employment Termination / Resignation</h3> <ul> <li>You will automatically retire from the service of the company on attaining the age of 58 years.</li> <li>Unannounced absents for a long time beyond the period of pre authorized leave shall be considered as you having voluntarily terminated your employment contract without giving any notice.</li> <li>Your services are liable to be terminated without any notice or salary in lieu thereof for mis- conduct, moral turpitude, any act of indiscipline, inefficiency and repeated non-performance in- spite of consistent warnings.</li> <li>On satisfactory completion of your probation period and after completing the minimum commitment period of 1 year to 1.5 year (as predefined at the time of joining) except for the reasons mentioned in appointment letter, your services can be terminated by giving notice of two months or payment of salary in lieu thereof on either side. However, in the event of your resignation, the company in its sole discretion will have an option to accept the same and relieve you prior to completion of the stipulated notice period to Two Months, without any pay in lieu of the notice period. Neither will leaves be granted nor any leave balance be adjusted during the notice period. During probation if either of the parties want to terminate employment then either they need to serve a notice period of 15 days or pay 15 days salary in lieu thereof. No resignations will be accepted in the months of March, April, December and January. A resignation shall be accepted from the date a resignation is applied irrespective of the date of acceptance.</li> </ul> <h3 id="notice_period_policy" style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">Notice Period Policy</h3> <p>The notice period is maximum 60 days for Band 3 and below and maximum 90 days for Band 4 and above. In case the employee cannot serve the complete notice period, he/she will have to pay The Company the gross salary in lieu of the remaining notice period. The applicability of notice period is from both sides, The Employee as well as from The Company. Under no circumstances will The Company’s accept “no proper handover”. Even if the payment in lieu of notice period is made, the Company’s still holds the right to accept/ reject the same. Some roles demand a proper notice to be served. Employees failing to serve the notice period and give a proper hand over will not be eligible for:</p> <ul> <li>Acknowledgement of Resignation Letter</li> <li>Experience Certificate</li> <li>Character Certificate</li> <li>Variables/ Incentives due</li> <li>Other Benefits due</li> </ul> <p><strong>The Company’s </strong> Management reserves the rights to relieve any employee, while the employee is still servicing his/her notice period earlier than the last working day of the employee’s notice period at their sole discretion. No payment will be made in such cases for the days when the employee was relieved earlier. A proper handover of tangible / intangible things need to be given to the assigned people to ensure a smooth Full &amp; Final Settlement of dues and documentation required. In case, if an employee has taken any loan / advance from the company and puts resignation, his / her resignation will be accepted only after the loan / advance amount is being paid back to The Company. The notice period will only start post payment of the Loan / advance to The Company. The last month’s salary of a notice period shall be settled with the Full and Final settlement process. A Full and Final settlement is executed after the notice period is served and is settled in maximum 45 days.</p> <h3 id="outside_employment_policy" style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">Outside Employment Policy</h3> <p>No outside employment activity shall take place during working hours or using the Company’s premises, supplies, or equipment. An employee may not engage oneself in any other activity, part-time or full-time, that generates a source of revenue or is indirect or indirect competition with the various activities that The Company provides to its clients.</p> <h3 id="employee_health_and_hygiene_policy" style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">Employee Health and Hygiene Policy</h3> <p>Employees are required to judge their health during illness &amp; decide themselves whether to attend the office or not. If any employee is found to be sick in such a manner that he/she might be risk to the health other employees, management reserves the right to ask such employees to go home &amp; recover from his or her illness this would be counted as a mandatory leave. Employees are required to keep the office premises clean, rough papers and things should be disposed in dustbins itself, pantry area should be kept cleaned after taking water and beverages.</p> <h3 id="employee_learning_and_development_policy" style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">Employee Learning &amp; Development Policy</h3> <p>Employees have to undergo some training sessions as decided &amp; arranged by the company &amp; need to complete the same in the given period of time during office hours or at home as directed by the management.</p> <h3 id="employee_transfer_policy" style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">Employee Transfer Policy</h3> <p>Employees can be transferred temporarily or permanently for duty anywhere in India, depending upon the needs of the organization. Your service may be transferred to any office of the Company or its associate organizations in India or abroad depending upon the exigencies of work. You will be governed by the transfer rules prevailing in the company at any given point of time.</p> <h3 id="expense_reimbursement_policy" style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">Expense Reimbursement Policy</h3> <ul> <li>All the RM’s will get a specific amount in the start of the month to manage the conveyance expenses carried to visit or handle clients.</li> <li>Apart from RM’s, employees needs to fill in a voucher for getting the reimbursement of their expenses done for official purposes.</li> <li>Employee needs to use local transport while going for any official work or client meetings. No use of personal vehicles to be done.</li> <li>Please take prior written permission from the Management in emergency cases before using your personal vehicle for official purposes.</li> </ul> <h3 id="incentives_policy" style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">Incentives Policy</h3> <p>Every employee will be eligible for a SALES incentive on the commission decided by the company. That shall be communicated by the respective TL for better understanding and clarity.</p> <p>The pay out of incentives shall be done immediately once the client is on boarded. But, this incentive can be rolled back if case if the policy is being surrendered or is being discontinued within 5 years of sale. In this case the Incentives amount will be adjusted during the full &amp; final settlement of the concerned employee.</p> <h3 id="appraisal_policy" style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;">Appraisal Policy</h3> <p>The Appraisal for an employee will be done annually, but the reviews will be done semiannual basis</p> <p>Every September and March there will be a review done by the employees respective HOD and further shall be reviewed by the management and HR and then documented in the employees’ file.</p> </div> <div id="general" class="w3-container searchable-content" style="padding:16px; margin-left: 250px;"> <h2 style="font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif; color: rgb(30, 136, 229); border-bottom-width: 2px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: rgb(255, 152, 0);">General Do's &amp; Don't's</h2> <table class="w3-table w3-bordered w3-striped w3-hoverable"> <thead> <tr> <th>Do's</th> <th>Don't's</th> </tr> </thead> <tbody> <tr> <td>Make sure that you treat this office as your own home and maintain cleanliness like at your home.</td> <td>Wait for anyone to point out to you for cleaning your desk/keeping your utensils etc.</td> </tr> <tr> <td>If you are heating food in the microwave and if there is spillage, please clean it immediately.</td> <td>Leave any eatables/used utensils/polythene bags on lunch table.</td> </tr> <tr> <td>Throw wet waste only in big dustbin.</td> <td>Throw any wet waste in the small dustbins.</td> </tr> <tr> <td>Use only one cup assigned to you for tea/coffee. If you need to use it again, please wash and re-use.</td> <td>Waste water.</td> </tr> <tr> <td>At the end of your day, before you leave office, please make sure that you keep any cups/glasses/plates/spoons or any other cutlery used into the sink.</td> <td>Use office property like printer, papers, stationery for personal use.</td> </tr> <tr> <td>Before keeping your utensils in sink, please make sure to rinse your utensil with water and throw any left-over in your plate into the big dustbin.</td> <td>Wear torn clothes/shorts and come to office.</td> </tr> <tr> <td>If you use any tissue papers, please make sure to throw the same in dustbin post use.</td> <td>Keep loud or filmy/funny ringtones in your mobile while in office premises.</td> </tr> <tr> <td>Switch off lights, fans, AC’s when not in use.</td> <td>Take personal calls while in office unless it is an emergency and are a short call.</td> </tr> <tr> <td>When using the washroom, ensure that before you leave the washroom, check if you have left any stains. If yes, kindly clean and then leave.</td> <td>Use social media for personal use beyond your break time.</td> </tr> <tr> <td>Before you leave the office, make sure that your workplace is clean (no scattered papers, etc.).</td> <td>Gossip in office premises and hours!</td> </tr> <tr> <td>Use your common sense when in doubt. If common sense does not work, ASK!</td> <td></td> </tr> </tbody> </table> </div> </div> <script> // Script to open and close sidebar function w3_open() { document.getElementById("mySidebar").style.display = "block"; document.getElementById("myOverlay").style.display = "block"; } function w3_close() { document.getElementById("mySidebar").style.display = "none"; document.getElementById("myOverlay").style.display = "none"; } function toggleAboutMenu() { var x = document.getElementById("aboutMenu"); if (x.className.indexOf("w3-show") == -1) { x.className += " w3-show"; } else { x.className = x.className.replace(" w3-show", ""); } } function toggleHRPoliciesMenu() { var x = document.getElementById("hrPoliciesMenu"); if (x.className.indexOf("w3-show") == -1) { x.className += " w3-show"; } else { x.className = x.className.replace(" w3-show", ""); } } function toggleOtherPoliciesMenu() { var x = document.getElementById("otherPoliciesMenu"); if (x.className.indexOf("w3-show") == -1) { x.className += " w3-show"; } else { x.className = x.className.replace(" w3-show", ""); } } var toggles = document.getElementsByClassName("toggle-button"); for (var i = 0; i < toggles.length; i++) { toggles[i].addEventListener("click", function() { var contentId = this.getAttribute("href").substring(1); var content = document.getElementById(contentId); if (content.className.indexOf("show") == -1) { content.className += " show"; } else { content.className = content.className.replace(" show", ""); } }); } // function searchContent() { //   let searchInput = document.getElementById('search').value.toLowerCase(); //   let contents = document.getElementsByClassName('searchable-content'); //   Array.from(contents).forEach(function(content) { //     let text = content.textContent.toLowerCase(); //     if (text.includes(searchInput)) { //       content.style.display = ''; //     } else { //       content.style.display = 'none'; //     } //   }); // } function searchContent() { // Get the search input and convert to lowercase let searchInput = document.getElementById('search').value.toLowerCase(); let contents = document.getElementsByClassName('searchable-content'); let found = false; // Flag to check if any section is found // Loop through each content section Array.from(contents).forEach(function(content) { let headingsH2 = content.getElementsByTagName('h2'); let headingsH3 = content.getElementsByTagName('h3'); let paragraphs = content.getElementsByTagName('p'); let isVisible = false; // Flag to check if the current section should be visible // Check h2 headings for the search term Array.from(headingsH2).forEach(function(heading) { let txtValue = heading.textContent.toLowerCase(); if (txtValue.includes(searchInput)) { isVisible = true; if (!found) { // Scroll to the first match and highlight heading.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'start' }); heading.classList.add('highlight'); setTimeout(() => heading.classList.remove('highlight'), 3000); // Remove highlight after 3 seconds found = true; } } }); // Check h3 headings for the search term Array.from(headingsH3).forEach(function(heading) { let txtValue = heading.textContent.toLowerCase(); if (txtValue.includes(searchInput)) { isVisible = true; if (!found) { // Scroll to the first match and highlight heading.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'start' }); heading.classList.add('highlight'); setTimeout(() => heading.classList.remove('highlight'), 3000); // Remove highlight after 3 seconds found = true; } } }); // Check paragraphs for the search term Array.from(paragraphs).forEach(function(paragraph) { let txtValue = paragraph.textContent.toLowerCase(); if (txtValue.includes(searchInput)) { isVisible = true; } }); // Toggle visibility of content sections content.style.display = isVisible ? '' : 'none'; }); // Alert if no matching content is found } function scrollToTop() { window.scrollTo({ top: 0, behavior: 'smooth' }); } window.onscroll = function() { var upButton = document.querySelector('.up-button'); if (document.body.scrollTop > 20 || document.documentElement.scrollTop > 20) { upButton.classList.add('show'); } else { upButton.classList.remove('show'); } }; function filterContent() { var input, filter, container, sections, i, txtValue; input = document.getElementById('search'); filter = input.value.toUpperCase(); container = document.getElementById('hr_policies'); sections = container.getElementsByClassName('policy-section'); // Loop through all policy sections and hide those that do not match the search query Array.from(sections).forEach(function(section) { var headings = section.getElementsByTagName('h3'); var paragraphs = section.getElementsByTagName('p'); var isVisible = false; // Check if the heading or paragraph matches the search query Array.from(headings).forEach(function(heading) { txtValue = heading.textContent || heading.innerText; if (txtValue.toUpperCase().indexOf(filter) > -1) { isVisible = true; } }); Array.from(paragraphs).forEach(function(paragraph) { txtValue = paragraph.textContent || paragraph.innerText; if (txtValue.toUpperCase().indexOf(filter) > -1) { isVisible = true; } }); // Show or hide the section based on visibility if (isVisible) { section.style.display = ''; } else { section.style.display = 'none'; } }); } </script> <div class="row sectionBlockLayout text-start" style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; margin: 0px; min-height: auto; padding: 8px;"> <div class="container" style="padding: 0px; display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap;"><div class="col-lg-12 columnBlockLayout" style="flex-grow: 1; display: flex; flex-direction: column; min-width: 250px;"></div></div> </div>
<script>
(function () {
  function toggleMenu(id) {
    var el = document.getElementById(id);
    if (!el) return;
    if (el.className.indexOf('w3-show') === -1) {
      el.className += ' w3-show';
    } else {
      el.className = el.className.replace(' w3-show', '');
    }
  }

  window.toggleAboutMenu = function () { toggleMenu('aboutMenu'); };
  window.toggleHRPoliciesMenu = function () { toggleMenu('hrPoliciesMenu'); };
  window.toggleOtherPoliciesMenu = function () { toggleMenu('otherPoliciesMenu'); };

  window.searchContent = function () {
    var input = document.getElementById('search');
    if (!input) return;
    var searchInput = input.value.toLowerCase().trim();
    var contents = document.getElementsByClassName('searchable-content');

    Array.prototype.forEach.call(contents, function (content) {
      if (!searchInput) {
        content.style.display = '';
        return;
      }

      var headingsH2 = content.getElementsByTagName('h2');
      var headingsH3 = content.getElementsByTagName('h3');
      var paragraphs = content.getElementsByTagName('p');
      var isVisible = false;

      Array.prototype.forEach.call(headingsH2, function (heading) {
        if (heading.textContent.toLowerCase().indexOf(searchInput) > -1) {
          isVisible = true;
        }
      });

      Array.prototype.forEach.call(headingsH3, function (heading) {
        if (heading.textContent.toLowerCase().indexOf(searchInput) > -1) {
          isVisible = true;
        }
      });

      Array.prototype.forEach.call(paragraphs, function (paragraph) {
        if (paragraph.textContent.toLowerCase().indexOf(searchInput) > -1) {
          isVisible = true;
        }
      });

      content.style.display = isVisible ? '' : 'none';
    });
  };

  var toggles = document.getElementsByClassName('toggle-button');
  Array.prototype.forEach.call(toggles, function (toggle) {
    toggle.addEventListener('click', function (e) {
      e.preventDefault();
      var href = this.getAttribute('href') || '';
      if (href.indexOf('#') !== 0) return;
      var contentId = href.substring(1);
      var content = document.getElementById(contentId);
      if (!content) return;
      var isHidden = content.style.display === 'none' || getComputedStyle(content).display === 'none';
      content.style.display = isHidden ? 'block' : 'none';
    });
  });

  var searchButton = document.querySelector('.search-button');
  if (searchButton) {
    searchButton.addEventListener('click', function (e) {
      e.preventDefault();
      window.searchContent();
    });
  }
})();
</script></body>
</html>
